-Hamiltonian\ndiffeomorphisms carries two bi-invariant norms, the cosymplectic analogues of\nthe usual symplectic capacity-inequality are derived and the cosymplectic\nanalogues of a result that was proved by Hofer-Zehnder follow.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Dec 2019 06:22:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 29 Dec 2019 12:29:53 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 6 Jan 2020 11:03:55 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Thu, 30 Apr 2020 20:19:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-04"}
