esolution of\nR$\\simeq$50-300, and a 25m$^2$ collecting area, would be capable of detecting\nH$_2$O, CO$_2$, CH$_4$, O$_3$, and N$_2$O in the atmosphere of an Earth-analog\ntransiting a M-dwarf (mag$_{K}=8.0$) within 50 transits, and obtain better than\nan order-of-magnitude constraint on each of their abundances.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 23 Dec 2019 15:58:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-04"}
